Patch: Fix TextArea undo/redo crash (ValueError: line index out of bounds)

In both _undo_batch() and _redo_batch(), _refresh_size() was called before
edit.after(), which updates the cursor position. The refresh triggers a
scrollbar update chain that reads the (now stale) cursor location, crashing
when an undo reduces the document to fewer lines than the cursor points to.

Fix: run edit.after() first so the cursor is valid before the UI refresh.

Affects: textual >= 7.4.0 (including 8.0.2 as of 2026-03-05)
Upstream: not yet fixed — consider filing at github.com/Textualize/textual

To apply:
  SITE=$(python -c "import textual; print(textual.__file__.rsplit('/',2)[0])")
  patch -p3 -d "$SITE" < 0011-fix-textarea-undo-cursor-crash.patch
